{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ddefc9ea-6e5b-4f70-9c19-4f01bfe78dad","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 with .NET 9. Here's the recommended pattern using **constructor injection** for `TestContext` plus both sync and async initialization:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (MSTest v3+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous init here (lightweight setup)\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // Async per-test initialization (DB connections, HTTP clients, etc.)\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor injection** of `TestContext` is available in MSTest v3+. No need for the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property.\n- Use the **constructor** for synchronous, lightweight setup (field assignment, simple config).\n- Use **`[TestInitialize]`** with an `async Task` signature for async setup (I/O, service connections).\n- The execution order is: Constructor → `[TestInitialize]` → Test → `[TestCleanup]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"99d611da-9fe3-456a-bcce-bd31a3bef572","outputTokens":373,"requestId":"843C:729EF:203CF5A:23A790C:6A0AD2C9"},"id":"78e0a51b-bcdf-4ae3-bd20-527b5c6cc71f","timestamp":"2026-05-18T08:50:26.991Z","parentId":"e21340c6-8345-44ab-a452-dbe3b6171602"}
